Cache previously determined sample file offset to fix performance issue with huge chunks.

Usually, MP4 files consist of several chunks with at most a few dozen samples each. However, I recently came across a file containing only a single chunk with millions of samples.

Accessing these samples was extremely slow as MP4Track::GetSampleFileOffset() summarizes the sample sizes from the beginning of the chunk each time a sample offset is requested.

This change fixes this by caching the previous result and then starting from there when another sample from the same chunk is requested.
